               <p>2249. <persName id="def1-2249-18370918" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-2249-18370918" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2249-18370918" type="age" value="16"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2249-18370918" type="surname" value="ARNOLD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2249-18370918" type="given" value="ROBERT JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2249-18370918" type="occupation" value="apprentice"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">ROBERT JOHN ARNOLD</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18370918-2249-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18370918-2249-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18370918-2249-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="stealingFromMaster"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18370918-cd-187" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370918-2249-offence-1 t18370918-cd-187"></join>2nd of September</rs>, 1 shilling, the money of <persName id="t18370918-name-1227" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1227" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1227" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1227" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1227" type="occupation" value="pawnbroker"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18370918-2249-offence-1 t18370918-name-1227"></join>Joseph Davis</persName> and another his masters.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1228" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1228" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1228" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1228" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH DAVIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker, and live at Woolwich—I am in partnership with Lewis Davis—the prisoner was my apprentice. On the 2nd of September I found in his coat pocket, which was in his box, one sovereign, one crown, nine half-crowns, and four shillings—I put it back, and my shopman marked some money.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1229" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1229" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1229" type="surname" value="JACOBS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1229" type="given" value="CHARLES SOLOMON"></interp>CHARLES SOLOMON JACOBS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the prosecutor's shopman. I marked two shillings, and placed them on a ledge over the till, on Saturday morning, the 2nd of September, about eleven o'clock—about four o'clock I missed one—it was found in the prisoner's pocket, by Mr. Davis and my self—this is one of the shillings—I said nothing to the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What was this boy? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> As apprentice—he never took in pledges—his duty was to keep the pledges in order in the warehouse—they want moving about continually—he has never taken in pledges, to my knowledge—I have been absent, and let him in the shop—if Mr. Davis was not in the shop, the prisoner was in call some one.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1230" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1230" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1230" type="surname" value="CHITTENDEN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1230" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS CHITTENDEN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a Woolwich police-constable. I took the prisoner, and have the shilling.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1231" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1231" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1231" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1231" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH DAVIS</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. The prisoner had no authority to receive pledges, but to receive money for goods that were sold—he might have had the opportunity of taking the shilling in giving change—he had as access to the till—he ought to have come to me, or our shopmen and asked for change—I was in town between eleven and four o'clock, on the 2nd of September—I cannot tell who was there that the prisoner might go to—the ledge is the general place where money is put for things that were sold—for change he would go to the pledge-counter, and ask the young men for it—he had a right to go there.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18370918-2249-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-2249-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-2249-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="withRecommendation"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 16.—<hi rend="italic">Recommended to mercy by the Jury and Prosecutor</hi>. 
<rs id="t18370918-2249-punishment-196" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18370918-2249-punishment-196" type="punishmentCategory" value="imprison"></interp>
